---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import TimeLineElement from "../components/cv/TimeLine.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="Resume" sideBarActiveItemID="cv">
  <div class="mb-5">
    <div class="text-3xl w-full font-bold">Professional Summary</div>
  </div>

  <div class="mb-10 text-justify">
    Geospatial Systems Engineer and Full-Stack Developer specializing in bridging enterprise spatial data with serverless cloud 
architecture. Proven track record of reducing manual assessment times by 99%, building high-performance web applications, 
and driving organic products to Page 1 of Google Search.
  </div>

  <div class="mb-5">
    <div class="text-3xl w-full font-bold">Education</div>
  </div>

  <div class="time-line-container grid gap-4 mb-10">
    <TimeLineElement
      title="Bachelor of Geographical Information Systems, majoring in Criminology"
      subtitle="2011 to 2015 at Flinders University, Adelaide, Australia"
    />
  </div>

  <div class="mb-5">
    <div class="text-3xl w-full font-bold">Experience</div>
  </div>

  <div class="time-line-container mb-10">
    <TimeLineElement
      title="Independent Development"
      subtitle="From Dec 2025 to Current, Independent, Adelaide, Australia"
    >
      <a href="https://AmIBetterOff.au">AmIBetterOff.au</a><br>
      • Engineered a serverless financial modelling application using Cloudflare Workers and pure HTML, CSS, JS<br>
      • Processed dynamic tax and contract calculations at the edge with near-zero latency<br>
      • Executed an organic SEO strategy securing Page 1 Google Search rankings<br>
      • Scaled platform to 4,000+ monthly active users with zero hosting costs<br>

      <a href="https://github.com/BriceNairn/news-reach">News-Reach</a><br>
      • Developed a real-time global event map using React and Leaflet<br>
      • Ingested and parsed massive data streams from global GDELT Project<br>
      • Designed automated serverless pipelines to handle 15-minute data deltas<br>
      • Implemented client-side spatial clustering for high-density geographic nodes<br>

    </TimeLineElement>
    <TimeLineElement
      title="Application Specialist (Enterprise), Contractor"
      subtitle="From Aug 2025 to Dec 2025 at SA Power Networks, Adelaide, Australia"
    >
      • Supported ArcGIS Enterprise and Azure-hosted GIS platforms across DEV, QAS and PRD environments, ensuring reliability of critical enterprise spatial systems<br>
      • Developed and enhanced FME Flow automations, resolving recurring failures and improving reliability of enterprise spatial data workflows<br>
      • Led cross-functional collaboration to resolve complex application issues, including coordinating a working group that cleared more than 30 outstanding support dependencies<br>

    </TimeLineElement>
    <TimeLineElement
      title="Founding Engineer (GIS)"
      subtitle="From Sep 2024 to Jun 2025 at SIMUNYE, Adelaide, Australia"
    >
      • Designed and built a Python-based geospatial automation platform that reduced manual assessment effort from 240+ hours to under one hour<br>
      • Led product development from concept to delivery, defining the technical architecture, service model, and commercial proposition<br>

    </TimeLineElement>
    <TimeLineElement
      title="Geospatial Data Analyst"
      subtitle="From May 2022 to Sep 2024 at Mott MacDonald, Adelaide, Australia"
    >
      • Delivered spatial analysis and decision-support mapping for major transport infrastructure, planning, and engineering projects across multidisciplinary teams<br>
      • Designed and administered project GIS platforms, web applications, and user access management to support collaboration between technical and non-technical stakeholders<br>
      • Built automated multi-criteria assessment and spatial analysis models using ArcGIS ModelBuilder, reducing manual effort and improving repeatability<br>

    </TimeLineElement>
    <TimeLineElement
      title="Facilities Information Officer, Contractor"
      subtitle="From Mar 2017 to Mar 2022 at SA Power Networks, Adelaide, Australia"
    >
      • Maintained electrical utility network asset records in GIS, translated As Constructed technical drawings into digital records<br>

    </TimeLineElement>
    <TimeLineElement
      title="3D & Orthophotography Technician"
      subtitle="From Aug 2015 to Jun 2016 at Aerometrex, Adelaide, Australia"
    >
      
    </TimeLineElement>
    
  </div>

  <div class="mb-5">
    <div class="text-3xl w-full font-bold">Certifications</div>
  </div>

  <ul class="list-disc mx-6 mb-10 grid gap-2">
    <li>
      FME Form Intermediate
    </li>
    <li>
      FME Form Basic
    </li>
  </ul>

  <div class="mb-5">
    <div class="text-3xl w-full font-bold">Skills</div>
  </div>

  <ul class="list-disc md:columns-5 columns-2 mx-6">
       
    <li>ArcGIS Enterprise (Portal, Server)</li>
    <li>ArcGIS Online (AGOL)</li>
    <li>ArcGIS Pro</li>
    <li>QGIS</li>
    <li>ArcPy</li>
    <li>FME Flow</li>

    <li>Python</li>
    <li>SQL</li>
    <li>PostgreSQL</li>
    <li>ETL/ELT</li>
    <li>Statistics</li>
    <li>Data Visualisation</li>
    <li>PowerBI</li>
    
    <li>Azure</li>
    <li>Azure DevOps</li>
    
    <li>HTML</li>
    <li>CSS</li>
    <li>JavaScript</li>
    <li>Cloudflare Workers</li>
    <li>GitHub</li>

    <li>Product Development</li>
    <li>Solution Design</li>
    <li>Technical Architecture</li>
    
  </ul>
</BaseLayout>
